text.section:
A modified administration shall be revoked by the:
Filing of a timely request for judicial probate;
Filing of a written objection by an interested person;
Filing of a withdrawal of the election for modified administration by a personal representative;
Orphans' Court, on its own initiative, or for good cause shown by an interested person or by the register of wills;
Failure to timely file the final report under modified administration and make timely distribution; or
Failure by the personal representative to comply with any provision of this subtitle.
